cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.DS 

This paper is about learning to rank, which is a subfield of information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is the most likely category. The paper also proposes a new approach to ListNet, a popular learning to rank model, which involves stochastic gradient descent and partial ranking information. This suggests that the paper may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) categories. Additionally, the paper uses experiments with image datasets, indicating that it may also belong to computer vision (cs.CV) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) categories.
